{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=June 2018}} '''Vidya Subramaniam''' ({{lang-ta|வித்யா சுப்ரமணியம்}}, born 1957) is a [[Tamil people|Tamil]] author. She has been writing [[novel]]s and [[Short story|short stories]] for close to three decades. Born and brought up in [[Mylapore]], she has to her credit 100 books and has won awards including a [[Tamil Nadu]] State Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pustakalibrary.in/vidhya-subramaniam?field_language_tid=All&page=2|title=Vidhya Subramaniam |publisher=Pustaka library|accessdate=26 March 2015 |language=}}</ref>
An anthology of her short stories has been translated into English titled ''Beyond the Frontier''. Two of her short stories have also been translated and featured in a book titled ''Anthology of Tamil [[Pulp magazine|Pulp Fiction]]'' from the Blaft stable.<ref>{{cite book | last = Chakravarthy | first = Pritham | title = The Blaft Anthology of Tamil Pulp Fiction | origyear = | month = | url = | accessdate = | edition = | series = | date = | year = 2008 | publisher = Blaft Publications | location = Chennai, India | isbn = 978-81-906056-0-1 | pages = 178 | chapter = | chapterurl = | quote = | ref = }}</ref>
